I like him.

1054
01:08:51,700 --> 01:08:56,700
Did you tell him to say did you enjoy it when you were in?

1055
01:08:56,700 --> 01:08:57,700
I like him.

1056
01:08:57,700 --> 01:09:00,700
Did you hear him talking back to the officers?

1057
01:09:00,700 --> 01:09:03,700
Oh yeah.

1058
01:09:03,700 --> 01:09:04,700
What do you remember?

1059
01:09:04,700 --> 01:09:07,700
What else do you remember about Freedom Day?

1060
01:09:07,700 --> 01:09:09,700
Freedom Day.

1061
01:09:09,700 --> 01:09:12,700
It was Poin Down Ring.

1062
01:09:12,700 --> 01:09:17,700
And police didn't have no...

1063
01:09:17,700 --> 01:09:20,700
Rain gear.

1064
01:09:20,700 --> 01:09:27,700
One of the stores downtown gave them all rain coats.

1065
01:09:27,700 --> 01:09:33,700
And that's how they stayed out there all day in that rain.

1066
01:09:33,700 --> 01:09:35,700
But it was...

1067
01:09:35,700 --> 01:09:40,700
You just felt like you was free, you know?

1068
01:09:40,700 --> 01:09:46,700
And I was talking to one writer.

1069
01:09:46,700 --> 01:09:51,700
He said, why were you out there?

1070
01:09:51,700 --> 01:09:57,700
I was getting my freedom.

1071
01:09:57,700 --> 01:10:04,700
And Jerry Nash.

1072
01:10:04,700 --> 01:10:08,700
He thought that was the funnest thing.

1073
01:10:08,700 --> 01:10:11,700
Getting my freedom.

1074
01:10:11,700 --> 01:10:16,700
Did any of the people coming into town doing the ministers?

1075
01:10:16,700 --> 01:10:19,700
Did they stay with you or any of you?

1076
01:10:19,700 --> 01:10:20,700
Oh yeah.

1077
01:10:20,700 --> 01:10:25,700
It's a lot of people came to Rep. John Conyers Jr.

1078
01:10:25,700 --> 01:10:28,700
He stayed at my house.

1079
01:10:28,700 --> 01:10:32,700
And I was told after was...

1080
01:10:32,700 --> 01:10:36,700
FBI agents stayed.

1081
01:10:36,700 --> 01:10:40,700
I guess they wanted to make sure nothing happened to the congressman.

1082
01:10:40,700 --> 01:10:47,700
So it was fun.

1083
01:10:47,700 --> 01:10:55,700
And I didn't have to be a street skater.

1084
01:10:55,700 --> 01:10:58,700
And my dad would take shifts.

1085
01:10:58,700 --> 01:11:02,700
You know, he'd stay up.

1086
01:11:02,700 --> 01:11:09,700
My mother would go to bed early and he would get up and stay up at...

1087
01:11:09,700 --> 01:11:15,700
He had been paralyzed, but he started walking and he had a cane.

1088
01:11:15,700 --> 01:11:18,700
And the cane was the man across us.

1089
01:11:18,700 --> 01:11:23,700
And people put out that old man sitting there with a shotgun across his leg.

1090
01:11:23,700 --> 01:11:28,700
Probably got me a day, put that out.

1091
01:11:28,700 --> 01:11:30,700
Yeah.

1092
01:11:30,700 --> 01:11:32,700
That was the word.

1093
01:11:32,700 --> 01:11:34,700
He was sitting there with a shotgun.

1094
01:11:34,700 --> 01:11:38,700
Did you get threatened with people threatening you?

1095
01:11:38,700 --> 01:11:41,700
Nobody threatened me.

1096
01:11:41,700 --> 01:11:49,700
But after we come back from watching, from New Jersey,

1097
01:11:49,700 --> 01:11:53,700
and you know who we went up there to?

1098
01:11:53,700 --> 01:11:56,700
Atlantic City.

1099
01:11:56,700 --> 01:12:05,700
And Los Angeles.

1100
01:12:05,700 --> 01:12:08,700
And you asked if you were threatened.

1101
01:12:08,700 --> 01:12:11,700
Oh, I was going to tell you.

1102
01:12:11,700 --> 01:12:15,700
I'd never been on my airplane before my life.

1103
01:12:15,700 --> 01:12:19,700
And we were campaigning for...

1104
01:12:19,700 --> 01:12:24,700
Me and the main Johnson.

1105
01:12:24,700 --> 01:12:27,700
And I went to New York.

1106
01:12:27,700 --> 01:12:32,700
Johnny Cameron went to Philadelphia, I think it was.

1107
01:12:32,700 --> 01:12:43,700
And just different, one of the delegates, we went to other states campaigning for him.

1108
01:12:43,700 --> 01:12:49,700
My telephone bill, I had got a telephone about that time.

1109
01:12:49,700 --> 01:12:58,700
But anyway, they knew I had got on the phone, somebody.

1110
01:12:58,700 --> 01:13:04,700
I mean, they got on the plane and daddy asked us to phone.

1111
01:13:04,700 --> 01:13:09,700
And they told us that our telephone bill is due.

1112
01:13:09,700 --> 01:13:15,700
It didn't have to be paid back by the clock, or we couldn't get out.

1113
01:13:15,700 --> 01:13:21,700
It's one of the things my daddy just wouldn't pay to be here.

1114
01:13:21,700 --> 01:13:24,700
I don't think it was about $15.

1115
01:13:24,700 --> 01:13:25,700
Yeah.

1116
01:13:25,700 --> 01:13:28,700
And it wouldn't be the problem.

1117
01:13:28,700 --> 01:13:31,700
That was they were going to get you with that?

1118
01:13:31,700 --> 01:13:34,700
I guess, I don't know.

1119
01:13:34,700 --> 01:13:37,700
So I couldn't call back.

1120
01:13:37,700 --> 01:13:42,700
But I wasn't threatened.

1121
01:13:42,700 --> 01:13:51,700
And my daughter, when Felicia [Connor], when they desegregated [the] self-created [white] schools",

1122
01:13:51,700 --> 01:13:57,700
and she was six to integrate.

1123
01:13:57,700 --> 01:14:00,700
Yeah. Freedom of choice.

1124
01:14:00,700 --> 01:14:03,700
Did she want to do that?

1125
01:14:03,700 --> 01:14:05,700
She didn't know.

1126
01:14:05,700 --> 01:14:09,700
You know, back then, children did what you say to them.

1127
01:14:09,700 --> 01:14:11,700
And they didn't question.

1128
01:14:11,700 --> 01:14:18,700
And I said to myself, I had been out to California with my sister,

1129
01:14:18,700 --> 01:14:23,700
and what happened about that time?

1130
01:14:23,700 --> 01:14:27,700
So daddy told me I need to come home.

1131
01:14:27,700 --> 01:14:34,700
And I got home like two days before the registration would end.

1132
01:14:34,700 --> 01:14:41,700
And she was a little plump girl.

1133
01:14:41,700 --> 01:14:44,700
And she was just skipping all the way.

1134
01:14:44,700 --> 01:14:45,700
That's a lot of him.

1135
01:14:45,700 --> 01:14:50,700
She was a baby, don't know what I'm getting into.

1136
01:14:50,700 --> 01:14:53,700
And we went up to the old headless bird car.

1137
01:14:53,700 --> 01:14:55,700
It's burning.

1138
01:14:55,700 --> 01:14:57,700
It had a lot of...

1139
01:14:57,700 --> 01:15:01,700
You haven't got it fixed yet.

1140
01:15:01,700 --> 01:15:04,700
She went up there.

1141
01:15:04,700 --> 01:15:10,700
And I didn't even know that the school name.

1142
01:15:10,700 --> 01:15:14,700
I know it was on 7th Street, crossing Herkley.

1143
01:15:14,700 --> 01:15:16,700
It was the name Jefferson Davis Elementary School.

1144
01:15:16,700 --> 01:15:21,700
I did, but I had never paid no attention.

1145
01:15:21,700 --> 01:15:24,700
And so he said, what school...

1146
01:15:24,700 --> 01:15:28,700
What school you want to send that girl to?

1147
01:15:28,700 --> 01:15:31,700
I said, I don't know the name of it.

1148
01:15:31,700 --> 01:15:35,700
I said, but it's located across from Herkley.

1149
01:15:35,700 --> 01:15:39,700
He said, Jefferson Davis.

1150
01:15:39,700 --> 01:15:44,700
Are you ready to change my name?

1151
01:15:44,700 --> 01:15:48,700
Absolutely, okay.

1152
01:15:48,700 --> 01:15:49,700
She didn't know.

1153
01:15:49,700 --> 01:15:52,700
She just know she was changing school.

1154
01:15:52,700 --> 01:15:57,700
And she's talked to some of the white kids later.

1155
01:15:57,700 --> 01:16:00,700
After they graduated from high school and all.

1156
01:16:00,700 --> 01:16:04,700
They didn't know what was going on either.

1157
01:16:04,700 --> 01:16:09,700
After I come these strange children coming to my room late.

1158
01:16:09,700 --> 01:16:12,700
See, all the kids were in that classroom.

1159
01:16:12,700 --> 01:16:15,700
And then they take the children to...

1160
01:16:15,700 --> 01:16:18,700
They go to the black school first and then they carry them away?

1161
01:16:18,700 --> 01:16:19,700
No, no, no, no.

1162
01:16:19,700 --> 01:16:22,700
Parents had to bring them.

1163
01:16:22,700 --> 01:16:28,700
But they would hold those kids until all the white kids get in that class and that seat.

1164
01:16:28,700 --> 01:16:31,700
And then the teacher would walk on the end.

1165
01:16:31,700 --> 01:16:36,700
And then they would say, is that why they would do that?

1166
01:16:36,700 --> 01:16:38,700
I don't know.

1167
01:16:38,700 --> 01:16:40,700
Make sure there wasn't any fighting.

1168
01:16:40,700 --> 01:16:42,700
It wasn't nothing going on.

1169
01:16:42,700 --> 01:16:44,700
I tell you, he had his spirit.

1170
01:16:44,700 --> 01:16:45,700
Nothing happened.

1171
01:16:45,700 --> 01:16:49,700
So what did she think about going to the white school?

1172
01:16:49,700 --> 01:16:50,700
She didn't know.

1173
01:16:50,700 --> 01:16:52,700
Didn't pay her no attention.

1174
01:16:52,700 --> 01:16:57,700
She didn't know she was the only spot in there.

1175
01:16:57,700 --> 01:17:01,700
And the teacher said, she won't let you ignore.

1176
01:17:01,700 --> 01:17:03,700
She said, they might try something.

1177
01:17:03,700 --> 01:17:04,700
She will not let you.

1178
01:17:04,700 --> 01:17:07,700
She was in the air today.

1179
01:17:07,700 --> 01:17:10,700
She used the personality for it.

1180
01:17:10,700 --> 01:17:15,700
And she still that way.

1181
01:17:15,700 --> 01:17:22,700
So we started to talk about when you got arrested when you were picketing at the courthouse?

1182
01:17:23,700 --> 01:17:27,700
We picketing and they let us march around one time and come back.

1183
01:17:27,700 --> 01:17:32,700
And he said, I'm going to stop it right here.

1184
01:17:32,700 --> 01:17:35,700
You.

1185
01:17:35,700 --> 01:17:38,700
Marching mighty good, looking mighty good.

1186
01:17:38,700 --> 01:17:39,700
Good.

1187
01:17:39,700 --> 01:17:45,700
See how you can march back there to that house behind.

1188
01:17:45,700 --> 01:17:47,700
And he's talking about the jail.

1189
01:17:47,700 --> 01:17:48,700
The jail.

1190
01:17:48,700 --> 01:17:51,700
And I went in that jail, my own.

1191
01:17:51,700 --> 01:17:59,700
They tried to keep people with leadership away from the other people.

1192
01:17:59,700 --> 01:18:07,700
They moved me from the jail to the farm out there where they put people in work.

1193
01:18:07,700 --> 01:18:10,700
You know, to work to find.

1194
01:18:10,700 --> 01:18:12,700
It was in the city, though.

1195
01:18:12,700 --> 01:18:17,700
It's not far from where the police station is now.

1196
01:18:17,700 --> 01:18:23,700
You were a leader and you wanted to make sure you didn't organize everybody in jail.

1197
01:18:23,700 --> 01:18:28,700
Yes, I was out there.

1198
01:18:28,700 --> 01:18:30,700
It was quite a few.

1199
01:18:30,700 --> 01:18:31,700
I was out there.

1200
01:18:31,700 --> 01:18:34,700
They arrested 60 some people that morning.

1201
01:18:34,700 --> 01:18:38,700
And then some come that afternoon and they're ready to spend.

1202
01:18:38,700 --> 01:18:41,700
We ended up having about 100 people in there.

1203
01:18:41,700 --> 01:18:44,700
What was it like in jail?

1204
01:18:44,700 --> 01:18:46,700
We saw songs.

1205
01:18:46,700 --> 01:18:49,700
We told stories.

1206
01:18:49,700 --> 01:18:54,700
And the man was on one side and the well was on the other side.

1207
01:18:54,700 --> 01:19:00,700
And he put a dipper and water in the middle of the flow.

1208
01:19:00,700 --> 01:19:04,700
And that's how you drink your water.

1209
01:19:04,700 --> 01:19:08,700
And then you had to.

1210
01:19:08,700 --> 01:19:12,700
I don't even remember going to the bathroom that all.

1211
01:19:12,700 --> 01:19:16,700
I don't remember.

1212
01:19:16,700 --> 01:19:18,700
You were there a week right?

1213
01:19:18,700 --> 01:19:20,700
Yeah, it was that week.

1214
01:19:20,700 --> 01:19:22,700
I went.

1215
01:19:22,700 --> 01:19:25,700
I don't remember that.

1216
01:19:25,700 --> 01:19:29,700
They could.

1217
01:19:29,700 --> 01:19:32,700
Were you worried about your children when you were in jail?

1218
01:19:32,700 --> 01:19:34,700
No, I didn't worry about them.

1219
01:19:34,700 --> 01:19:40,700
I was going to tell them that.

1220
01:19:40,700 --> 01:19:43,700
What did your parents think about you being in the movie?

1221
01:19:43,700 --> 01:19:49,700
My mother.

1222
01:19:49,700 --> 01:19:51,700
She wasn't a said.

1223
01:19:51,700 --> 01:19:52,700
Nothing.

1224
01:19:52,700 --> 01:19:53,700
No way.

1225
01:19:53,700 --> 01:19:58,700
Because if John Henry was far, she's far too.

1226
01:19:58,700 --> 01:20:02,700
But we've been thinking, hill-aigling, you know.

1227
01:20:02,700 --> 01:20:07,700
She died in 86.

1228
01:20:07,700 --> 01:20:12,700
I don't think she ever attended Mass Meeting.

1229
01:20:12,700 --> 01:20:15,700
She stayed home.

1230
01:20:15,700 --> 01:20:20,700
And my children, they never attended Mass Meeting.

1231
01:20:20,700 --> 01:20:21,700
She would stay.

1232
01:20:21,700 --> 01:20:22,700
Just me and my dad.

1233
01:20:22,700 --> 01:20:25,700
But she came to the precinct meeting with you?

1234
01:20:25,700 --> 01:20:26,700
Oh, yes.

1235
01:20:26,700 --> 01:20:29,700
That's interesting.

1236
01:20:29,700 --> 01:20:32,700
But different thing.

1237
01:20:32,700 --> 01:20:37,700
Precinct man, he was meeting with us in the daytime.

1238
01:20:37,700 --> 01:20:40,700
So you think she didn't want to go out at night?

1239
01:20:40,700 --> 01:20:42,700
Now, would your dad pick it with you?

1240
01:20:42,700 --> 01:20:44,700
Oh, yes, he'd pick it.

1241
01:20:44,700 --> 01:20:48,700
Your only came.

1242
01:20:48,700 --> 01:20:51,700
So you were a team.

1243
01:20:51,700 --> 01:20:55,700
You told me before that when you went to March in front of the courthouse

1244
01:20:55,700 --> 01:20:58,700
that you knew you were going to get arrested?

1245
01:20:58,700 --> 01:21:02,700
Yes, when we left the COFO office office,

1246
01:21:02,700 --> 01:21:05,700
we all gave that the COFO office office.

1247
01:21:05,700 --> 01:21:08,700
We walked up Moeville Street, the Batson Street,

1248
01:21:08,700 --> 01:21:12,700
and see Batson Street, right in front of the...

1249
01:21:12,700 --> 01:21:16,700
it runs out in front of the courthouse.

1250
01:21:16,700 --> 01:21:18,700
We didn't get in the street.

1251
01:21:18,700 --> 01:21:21,700
We walked on the sidewalk all the way.

1252
01:21:21,700 --> 01:21:24,700
And then we just ran out and started.

1253
01:21:24,700 --> 01:21:26,700
How did you know you were going to get arrested?

1254
01:21:26,700 --> 01:21:30,700
Because they had told us if you come up here,

1255
01:21:30,700 --> 01:21:32,700
you go into jail.

1256
01:21:32,700 --> 01:21:35,700
The last group that was up there the day before.

1257
01:21:35,700 --> 01:21:40,700
So you come again, you go into jail.

1258
01:21:40,700 --> 01:21:43,700
And you weren't worried about that?

1259
01:21:43,700 --> 01:21:46,700
Nine o'clock, we were ready.

1260
01:21:46,700 --> 01:21:50,700
So they thought that was going to be enough to stop you?

1261
01:21:50,700 --> 01:21:53,700
Yeah.

1262
01:21:53,700 --> 01:21:57,700
That's what they thought.

1263
01:21:57,700 --> 01:22:01,700
How did you end up getting out?

1264
01:22:01,700 --> 01:22:05,700
Mr. and Mrs.

1265
01:22:05,700 --> 01:22:11,700
with the name.

1266
01:22:11,700 --> 01:22:14,700
Thought I'd never forget that.

1267
01:22:14,700 --> 01:22:20,700
But anyway, they put their house $1,000.

1268
01:22:20,700 --> 01:22:24,700
All those people got that money back.

1269
01:22:24,700 --> 01:22:28,700
So if we had given them cash money, we wouldn't have.

1270
01:22:28,700 --> 01:22:32,700
Did you have to go to court for that?

1271
01:22:32,700 --> 01:22:34,700
No, I'd law you some hand.

1272
01:22:34,700 --> 01:22:36,700
You have always wanted to.

1273
01:22:36,700 --> 01:22:38,700
Did they get it thrown out?

1274
01:22:38,700 --> 01:22:39,700
Yeah.

1275
01:22:39,700 --> 01:22:42,700
Can you tell me about organizing the FTP?

1276
01:22:42,700 --> 01:22:45,700
Yes.

1277
01:22:45,700 --> 01:22:50,700
When I was in Dorchester Center,

1278
01:22:50,700 --> 01:23:02,700
Dorothy told us that we were going to try to attend the primary meetings.

1279
01:23:02,700 --> 01:23:08,700
And then after we couldn't...

1280
01:23:08,700 --> 01:23:13,700
It's SNCC's some of the smartest people.

1281
01:23:13,700 --> 01:23:16,700
You know?

1282
01:23:16,700 --> 01:23:21,700
They knew all along that we were going to try that.

1283
01:23:21,700 --> 01:23:26,700
And so we went to the...

1284
01:23:26,700 --> 01:23:30,700
tried to go to primary meetings.

1285
01:23:30,700 --> 01:23:33,700
And we didn't have poll tax.

1286
01:23:33,700 --> 01:23:39,700
I was the only one that really paid the poll tax.

1287
01:23:40,700 --> 01:23:44,700
And they shouldn't even be asking that at a present meeting.

1288
01:23:44,700 --> 01:23:51,700
We didn't talk nothing about who was going to vote for all.

1289
01:23:51,700 --> 01:23:54,700
You know, nothing.

1290
01:23:54,700 --> 01:24:01,700
So I...

1291
01:24:01,700 --> 01:24:10,700
The end of that 18 didn't have a one vote and that was my vote.

1292
01:24:10,700 --> 01:24:15,700
So I don't know what they were doing for a piece of second.

1293
01:24:15,700 --> 01:24:24,700
But I was elected to go to the county meeting with the other group.

1294
01:24:24,700 --> 01:24:28,700
And then...

1295
01:24:29,700 --> 01:24:33,700
When we got to the district meeting,

1296
01:24:33,700 --> 01:24:37,700
it was hell at the cold house too.

1297
01:24:37,700 --> 01:24:39,700
I didn't get no vote.

1298
01:24:39,700 --> 01:24:42,700
So that's what I got.

1299
01:24:42,700 --> 01:24:45,700
But...

1300
01:24:45,700 --> 01:24:52,700
But you know, I would be the only flat in no field, no field at all.

1301
01:24:52,700 --> 01:24:54,700
You just weren't worried about it?

1302
01:24:54,700 --> 01:24:57,700
I'm worried at all.

1303
01:24:57,700 --> 01:25:02,700
I know the good law was taking care of me.

1304
01:25:02,700 --> 01:25:05,700
I just...

1305
01:25:05,700 --> 01:25:08,700
He had to be...

1306
01:25:08,700 --> 01:25:12,700
Because he was all kind of clans up in the...

1307
01:25:12,700 --> 01:25:14,700
Did you ever...

1308
01:25:14,700 --> 01:25:17,700
Were the clans ever out when you were watching?

1309
01:25:17,700 --> 01:25:20,700
